            "content": {
                "raw": "I guess I didn't realize that Castro and maestro support in 2.x were broken.  Are they? Are they hard to support?  Is it that the format is changing frequently or something like that?  If it is stable, I don't know why we should be removing frontends from 2.x, but if it requires a lot of upkeep and it works in 3.0, then removing it makes sense.  I just want to make sure 2.x doesn't get pared down too much.\n\nSo what is the word?",
                "html": "<p>I guess I didn't realize that Castro and maestro support in 2.x were broken.  Are they? Are they hard to support?  Is it that the format is changing frequently or something like that?  If it is stable, I don't know why we should be removing frontends from 2.x, but if it requires a lot of upkeep and it works in 3.0, then removing it makes sense.  I just want to make sure 2.x doesn't get pared down too much.</p>\n<p>So what is the word?</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
