                    }
                },
                "id": 630
            },
            "content": {
                "raw": "Maestro has been turned off from `load` for quite some time - there was some confusion differentiating Maestro from other BoxLib datasets.  I *think* Castro worked okay, but there may have been some corner cases that confused it with Nyx or Orion.\n\nIn either case, @MatthewTurk did a great job of unifying the Boxlib-based frontends in 3.0.  I suspect @ngoldbaum was suggesting either those changes should be back-ported to the individual Maestro/Castro/Nyx/Orion frontends, or those that are broken in 2.x should be removed?\n\nI'm game for either setup, but thought I'd bring it up for discussion.",
                "html": "<p>Maestro has been turned off from <code>load</code> for quite some time - there was some confusion differentiating Maestro from other BoxLib datasets.  I <em>think</em> Castro worked okay, but there may have been some corner cases that confused it with Nyx or Orion.</p>\n<p>In either case, <a href=\"/MatthewTurk/\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"@MatthewTurk\" class=\"mention\">Matthew Turk</a> did a great job of unifying the Boxlib-based frontends in 3.0.  I suspect <a href=\"/ngoldbaum/\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"@ngoldbaum\" class=\"mention\">Nathan Goldbaum</a> was suggesting either those changes should be back-ported to the individual Maestro/Castro/Nyx/Orion frontends, or those that are broken in 2.x should be removed?</p>\n<p>I'm game for either setup, but thought I'd bring it up for discussion.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
