                "html": "<p>My feeling is very much like what <a href=\"/brittonsmith/\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"@brittonsmith\" class=\"mention\">Britton Smith</a> said.  2.6 is supposed to be a long-term support branch, and I think that removing unused, unsupported and potentially incorrectly-implemented frontends is going to improve the maintainability.  <a href=\"/ChrisMalone/\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"@ChrisMalone\" class=\"mention\">Chris Malone</a> , thanks for doing this!</p>",
